  "doc_id": "59083",
  "text": "Skin was reconstituted in nude mice as previously described, except for the addition of cells cultured in hydrogels [CITATION_1] . In the positive controls, 5 Â 10 6 freshly isolated dermal cells and 8 Â 10 6 epidermal cells were used per graft [CITATION_2] . In some experimental grafts, mice received 8 Â 10 6 epidermal cells and the intact hydrogel from one well of a 24-well plate. In other grafts, mice received 8 Â 10 6 epidermal cells, 5 Â 10 6 freshly isolated wildtype dermal cells, and 5 Â 10 3 cells (spheres and single cells) released from hydrogels (corresponding to 1-3 wells of a 24-well plate). The number of cultured cells was calculated by disaggregating spheres from replicate wells using trypsin/EDTA. Grafts were analyzed after 4-5 weeks.",
